5 Jul 2015 Haiti: NOTICE: Update of measures to prevent Ebola in Haiti
http://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-14425-haiti-notice-update-of-measures-to-prevent-ebola-in-haiti.html
[Following the appearance of new cases of Ebola in Liberia, Dr Florence D Guillaume, minister of public health and population (MSPP), in order to protect Haiti from the introduction of this viral disease on its territory, reports that the ministry decided to return this West African country (which had been withdrawn in May 2015) http://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-13955-haiti-notice-update-of-measures-against-ebola.html to the list of risk countries such as Sierra Leone and Guinea-Conakry.

The same recommendations are still in force, and all those who traveled in the countries mentioned will not be able and should not seek to return to Haiti before a minimum period of 21 days after leaving the affected country(ies).]

