6 Jul 2015 Liberia: Finance Ministry "hooked" in the management of over USD 200 million in GAC audit report
http://allafrica.com/stories/201507062874.html
[According to the Government of Liberia (GoL) Consolidated Fund Financial Statements by the General Auditing Commission (GAC), authorities of the Ministry of Finance and Development Planning (MFDP) in the management of the GoL Consolidated Funds were "marred with a number of irregularities and internal control deficiencies." These "financial irregularities and internal control deficiencies" totaled USD 210.2 million. They included the contractual payment to a fuel supplier without a valid contract for fuel supplied to the Ministry of Defense and the payment for domestic debt arrears without evidence of supporting documents.]

